WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:04.160
How can you solve addition problems?

2
00:00:05.150 --> 00:00:06.160
What do you see?

3
00:00:06.970 --> 00:00:09.499
Yellow counters and red counters.

4
00:00:10.540 --> 00:00:11.890
How many are yellow?

5
00:00:12.890 --> 00:00:24.745
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

6
00:00:25.545 --> 00:00:27.579
There are 8 yellow counters.

7
00:00:28.490 --> 00:00:29.718
How many are red?

8
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:37.304
1, 2, 3, 4, 5.

9
00:00:38.010 --> 00:00:40.145
There are 5 red counters.

10
00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:43.922
What does it mean to put the counters together?

11
00:00:46.780 --> 00:00:49.835
When you put yellow and red counters together,

12
00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:52.371
you make one group of counters.

13
00:00:53.140 --> 00:00:55.796
The circle is around all of the counters.

14
00:00:56.600 --> 00:00:59.862
It shows that the counters are being put together.

15
00:01:02.820 --> 00:01:05.068
Here are the same group of counters.

16
00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:06.921
What is different?

17
00:01:08.321 --> 00:01:15.090
The counters are lined up and they are in 10-frames.

18
00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.759
How can you tell the counters are being put together?

19
00:01:21.890 --> 00:01:27.052
2 red counters move to fill the first 10-frame.

20
00:01:29.610 --> 00:01:31.344
What does the equation tell?

21
00:01:32.100 --> 00:01:36.783
It shows the number in each group and how many in all

22
00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:38.315
when they are put together.

23
00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:43.914
8 plus 5 equals 13.

24
00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:50.946
Counting on is another way to find how many in all.

25
00:01:51.830 --> 00:01:53.264
Look at the number line.

26
00:01:53.870 --> 00:01:58.443
The number line shows 8 plus 5 equals 13.

27
00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:05.719
Start at one part, 8, and count on the other part, 5.

28
00:02:06.660 --> 00:02:08.420
The sum is 13.

29
00:02:09.229 --> 00:02:15.630
The number line and the equation both show that 8 plus 5 equals 13.